{
  "texts": [
    "Cross-Task GeneralizationThe consistent improvements across datasets confirm DRaFT-Q's generality.",
    "Rather than overfitting to a particular structure, it dynamically redistributes capacity layer-wise and sample-wise, reducing both overparameterization and underfitting.",
    "Its reward-weighted strategy further guides learning toward meaningful regions of the token space.Across all tasks, DRaFT-Q achieves the best performance without exceeding the compute or memory budgets of existing PEFT baselines.",
    "This validates our hypothesis that dynamic adaptation during training is critical for low-resource LLM fine-tuning.",
    "Evaluation Setup and SignificanceWe conduct all evaluations using consistent hyperparameters across methods to ensure fairness."
  ]
}